<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-6529] sstableloader shows no progress or errors when pointed at a bad directory</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-6529</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;With sstableloader, the source directory is supposed to be in the format &lt;tt&gt;&amp;lt;keyspace_name&amp;gt;/&amp;lt;table_name&amp;gt;/&lt;/tt&gt;.  If you incorrectly just put the sstables in a &lt;tt&gt;&amp;lt;keyspace_name&amp;gt;/&lt;/tt&gt; directory, the sstableloader process will not show any progress, errors, or other output, it will simply hang.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This was initially reported on the user ML here: &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.mail-archive.com/user@cassandra.apache.org/msg33916.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://www.mail-archive.com/user@cassandra.apache.org/msg33916.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
